mAPI-ng is an open-core project. It is NOT covered by a single license: each
Go module in this repository carries its own LICENSE file, and that per-module
license is authoritative. See docs/adr/0004-open-core-licensing.md for the
rationale.

  Module                                  Path        License
  --------------------------------------  ----------  ------------------------
  github.com/arhuman/maping/proto         proto/      MIT
  github.com/arhuman/maping/client        client/     MIT
  github.com/arhuman/maping/client/gin    client/gin/ MIT
  github.com/arhuman/maping/client/beego  client/beego/ MIT
  github.com/arhuman/maping/client/chi    client/chi/ MIT
  github.com/arhuman/maping/client/echo   client/echo/ MIT
  github.com/arhuman/maping/client/nethttp client/nethttp/ MIT
  github.com/arhuman/maping/server        server/     Business Source License 1.1
  github.com/arhuman/maping/example       example/    MIT

The client (and its adapters) and the shared proto module are MIT so they are
safe to import into production services. The server is source-available under
BSL 1.1 (self-hostable for non-competing use, converting to Apache 2.0 per its
Change Date). Refer to each module's LICENSE file for the exact terms.

